-century bishop of Myra in Lycia, about whom virtually nothing factual is known, although a vast body of legend grew up around him, and he became the patron saint of Greece and of Russia, as well as of children, sailors, merchants, and pawnbrokers. His feast day is  6 December , and among the many roles which legend has assigned to him is that of bringer of Christmas presents, in the guise of ‘Santa Claus’ (an alteration of the Dutch form of his name, <i>Sinterklaas</i>)."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Nicolaus Moltke was born about 1286, in Germany, his father, Georg Moltke, was 32 and his mother, Unknown, was 28. He married Kristine Sparre about 1315, in Germany. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1346, at the age of 61."},"et":{"ABOUT 1286–1346":"umbes 1286–1346","1286–1346":"1286–1346","1290–Female":"1290–Surnud","1316–1363":"1316–1363","1325–Male":"1325–Surnud","1256–Male":"1256–Surnud","1260–Female":"1260–Surnud","1316":"1316","abt 1325":"umbes 1325","1325":"1325","1346":"1346","about 1290":"umbes 1290","1256":"1256","Abt 1315":"umbes 1315","1363":"1363","1286":"1286","ABOUT 1286":"umbes 1286","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","Mecklenburg":"Saksamaa",",,, Germany":"Saksamaa","Germany":"Saksamaa"},"fi":{"ABOUT 1286–1346":"noin 1286–1346","1286–1346":"1286–1346","1290–Female":"1290–Kuollut","1316–1363":"1316–1363","1325–Male":"1325–Kuollut","1256–Male":"1256–Kuollut","1260–Female":"1260–Kuollut","1316":"1316","abt 1325":"noin 1325","1325":"1325","1346":"1346","about 1290":"noin 1290","1256":"1256","Abt 1315":"noin 1315","1363":"1363","1286":"1286","ABOUT 1286":"noin 1286","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","Mecklenburg":"Saksa",",,, Germany":"Saksa","Germany":"Saksa"},"fr":{"ABOUT 1286–1346":"environ 1286–1346","1286–1346":"1286–1346","1290–Female":"1290–Décédée","1316–1363":"1316–1363","1325–Male":"1325–Décédé","1256–Male":"1256–Décédé","1260–Female":"1260–Décédée","1316":"1316","abt 1325":"environ 1325","1325":"1325","1346":"1346","about 1290":"environ 1290",